CEZ AS (CEZ)  declined for a fifth day after
Lidove Noviny newspaper reported the biggest Czech power utility
may lose as much as 10 billion koruna ($515 million) in three
years on its investment in Albaniaâ€™s power-distribution company.  The stock dropped 1.3 percent to 711 koruna, poised for its
lowest close and the longest stretch of declines since November.
